deck: AC_OSORIO (Alberto Cortes) is an Illustrator, Graphic & Web Designer born and raised in Puerto Rico.
description:
AC_OSORIO (Alberto Cortes) is an Illustrator, Graphic & Web Designer born and raised in Puerto Rico. In 1997 during his studies in Marine Biology, AC worked as a Scientific Illustrator for 2 Field Guide Books inside the Marine Biology Department and Wildlife Management program. His B.A. in Marine Biology was received from Puerto Rico University in Humacao in 1999-2000.

As an Illustrator AC was very active in promoting and exposing his work through the Internet which led in 2006 a short story from Razor Blade Apple Comics (RBA COMICS) to be published under the title of RBA PRESENTS #4. Later, inside the studio, AC was offered a Sub Contract to work as a Colorist for Scare Tactix Graphix title KYU-SHIN. After a year of successfully meeting every deadline thrown, AC not only manages to win penciling chores inside RBA's top Title GUNBREED, but earn Active Partnership inside RBA Studios.

The continued work recognition landed in 2008 the opportunity to work with well know UK writer Richard James Johnson (The Enemy's Son), The short story, HERO IN HELL, was featured and published through Murky Depths Issue #8 in 2008/09.
name: AC Osorio

deck: Ivonne Falcon is a Comic book Illustrator based in Puerto Rico.
description:
Ivonne Falcón is a Puerto Rican artist. She illustrated Santa Cristal (2005), Kyu Shin (2009) for Scare Tactix Graphix, as well as several short stories for RBA Presents (2008-2010), and was cover artist for Leviathans (2009).

She illustrated Violet Descends (2010), a book she co-created with writer Angel Fuentes. As member of RBA Studios, she serves as Assistant Art Director . Ivonne has a Masters Degree in Graphic Art and Design.

Publish work includes KYU-SHIN from Scare Graphix Tactis & RBA Comics Violet Descends.
name: Ivonne Falcon

deck: Justin Sweet is a freelance artist noted for his work in the fantasy genre.
description:
Justin Sweet studied art at Cal State Fullerton and later worked for Black Isle studios.

He has done freelance work for various game and book publishers such as National Geographic, Wizards of the Coast, Tor, DelRey and Wandering Star.

Justin Sweet has also done concept work for production companies. Most notably for Disney on The Chronicles of Narnia and HBOs Game of Thrones.

Justin's work has been featured in Spectrum numerous times, from which he received both a gold and silver medal.
name: Justin Sweet

deck: Writer, graphic designer, layout artist, game designer.
description: Aaron Rosenberg is an award-winning novelist, game designer, comic book writer, and children's book author. He has written for Star Trek, WarCraft, Eureka, iCarly, and a variety of other properties, and has worked on games for Lord of the Rings, Deryni, and DC, among others. He is also a graphic designer and layout artist, and has designed books and covers for several companies and authors. Aaron created the roleplaying company Clockworks. He is also a founding member of Crazy 8 Press.
name: Aaron Rosenberg
